article.linkText: McKee scores 19, leads Queens University over Jacksonville 74-65
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — AJ McKee had 19 points to lead Queens University to a 74-65 victory over Jacksonville on Friday night. McKee added three steals for the Royals (11-17, 5-8 Atlantic Sun Conference). Deyton Albury scored 12 points with three steals. Jaxon Pollard scored 11. The Dolphins (13-14, 4-9) were led by Robert McCray with 22 points. Gyasi Powell added 12 points. Stephon Payne III pitched in with nine points and 12 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
